M1 money supply includes sum of currency available to Households and Businesses to make payments. US currencies and balances in checking and savings account are part of M1 calculations.

Marcoeconomic theory suggests that increase in money circulation leads to lower interest rates and higher borrowing / lending and consumer spending in the economy.
